Scene 4: MAGICAL FOREST - X:00 PM

John Bernoulli is walking.

ASSASSIN
Be careful! Don’t you know there's a beast around here that could have killed you?

JOHN BERNOULLI
Of course I know about the beast, that's the reason I’m here, to slay the beast and convince Korniss to send me home.

ASSASSIN
We may have the same goal, then. I also need to deal with the beast to prevent it from hurting more people.
(Pulls out two bottles)
I have this poison which should slay the beast, but I don’t know how I can give it to the beast.

JOHN BERNOULLI
Hmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmmm…
(Begins pacing)
You're an assassin, have you heard of the assassin’s teapot?

ASSASSIN
No, I’m not too up to date on the latest technology.

JOHN BERNOULLI
It's an ingenious invention, really, it uses a difference in air pressure and surface tension to allow one to alternate which liquid is being poured out of the teapot. It also never breaks.

ASSASSIN
So you propose we invite the beast for a delightful teatime, lower its guards by pouring our tea first, and then poison it with the torturous death poison. I like this plan.

John Bernoulli and the Assassin return to the place where they first met the beast and place an RSVP at the edge of the area. The Beast picks it up and looks briefly puzzled. Some time later The Beast arrives at the teaparty, where there is a well set table. John Bernoulli and the Assassin look frightened by Beast Alpha.

BEAST ALPHA
Excuse me, but was this the location where I was kindly invited to a most delightful tea party?

JB and A nod silently, still apprehensive about the beast.


BEAST ALPHA
Wonderful, it has been so long since I have had a well steeped sleepytime vanilla, I must confess to having missed it.

ASSASSIN
I had no idea you were such a tea fanatic.

BEAST ALPHA
Like I said, it's been some time. The Engineer who created and raised me used to make some wonderful brews. I… I miss him.

JOHN BERNOULLI
…Is that why you’ve been lashing out at people?

BEAST ALPHA
I suppose it is.
(The Beast pauses regretfully)
That now seems to be a rather harsh response.

ASSASSIN
Harsh!?! You’ve hurt countless people!

THE BEAST
I did, and for that I am sorry. I will do what I can in the future to right those wrongs.

John Bernoulli and the Assassin make eye contact and nod. The Assassin then pours tea into all three of the glasses. After drinking some tea the beast yawns loudly.

THE BEAST
I seem to be very tired, could I lay down here for a moment.

JOHN BERNOULLI
Of course, make yourself comfortable.

The Beast dozes off and begins snoring.

JOHN BERNOULLI
So what do you plan to do now, Assassin?

ASSASSIN
Well, if you wanted some help with the rest of the beasts, I don’t have anything better to do.

JB smiles and the two of them walk off into the next scene.
